Step 1. Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio  
• Total Liabilities are given by the “Total Current Liabilities”: 8,028,630.43  
• Total Assets: 39,772,748.32  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 8,028,630.43 / 39,772,748.32 ≈ 0.20  

Step 2. Calculate Gross Profit Margin  
• Gross Profit: 8,372,608.70  
• Total Revenue: 28,572,608.70  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (8,372,608.70 / 28,572,608.70) × 100% ≈ 29.30%  

Step 3. Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
• Operating Cash Flow (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities): –10,442,735.47  
• Total Current Liabilities (the denominator): 8,028,630.43  
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Total Current Liabilities  
  = (–10,442,735.47 / 8,028,630.43) ≈ –1.30  

Thus, the solution is:  

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.20",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "29.30%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-1.30"
  }
}
